Project 1 refers to the project with the ID of 1 in the projects table;
 comment count refers to the number of comments associated with each issue, with higher counts indicating more comments;
 'top 5 issues' refers to the 5 issues with the highest comment count, as determined by the ORDER BY and LIMIT clauses.

sql:
SELECT metric_name, metric_value
FROM issue_metrics
WHERE issue_id = 1;
